main event: Multiple reports were received from Denver Air Traffic Control and military personnel regarding a bright white streaking object observed in flight for a few seconds on 9 April 1964.
interesting points: The object moved westerly across the sky at a high speed., Witnesses included two supervisors from Denver Air Route Traffic Control Center., Reports of the object's effect on radio communications were received from New Mexico State Police., General Cabell observed the object at 0202 on 9 April., The object was described as a bright, flashing streak in the sky.
witnesses: Denver Air Route Traffic Control Center supervisors
